<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=391&amp;p=2669#p2669"><![CDATA[
Actually, the standard Arkanoid controller uses an [inverted] NINE-bit data signal where the minimum is 196 and the maximum is 484; evidently, the original used an oscillator (based on the resistance in the varister) and also relied on exactly 1/60th of a second between each strobe to get proper values.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Fri Jul 08, 2005 9:59 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
